Gadgetbahn (also Gadgetbahnen) is a [[pejorative]] term used by some [http://www.publictransit.us/PublicTransitUS.php?catid=20&blogid=8 transit professionals] to describe what they view as infeasible transportation concepts. It is a compounding of [[''gadget'']], meaning "''device that has a useful specific purpose and function''," and the German word ''bahn'', which has multiple meanings including ''way, lane, rail'' and ''tram.''

Perhaps the most well-known transportation concepts to be labeled as gadgetbahn are [[monorail]] and [[Personal Rapid Transit]].[http://www.planetizen.com/node/70]


